> People judge the randomness of a sequence by comparing its features to a subjective ideal using Bayesian smoothing, but they dynamically adjust their expected alternation rate downwards based on their smoothed estimate of the sequence's heads/tails balance, intuitively recognizing that imbalanced sequences must have fewer alternations.

